      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this the root bug, skcms_ApproximatelyEqual() rejecting profile pairs we should consider equal?  The issue is comparing a natively grayscale profile with a profile we\u0027ve translated from grayscale to RGB, right?  If we just let the transforms at the bottom of skcms_ApproximatelyEqual() run without short circuiting, wouldn\u0027t we see they end up with approximately equal XYZ outputs and decide it was fine?\n\n(I don\u0027t have any objection to using SkColorSpace::Equals() per se, and I think if it had been written this way without any comment it would have raised no eyebrows.)",
