      "writtenOn": "2020-07-30T19:58:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I keep getting tripped up why F16 is special at all in SkCodec.  Is it special in a way that F16Norm or F32 isn\u0027t?  I can\u0027t understand why any individual SkColorType would get its own control flow... is there some class of SkColorTypes we\u0027re trying to cover here?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 672,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 672,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "5f3d22204c3dfa974f432ed092042984250ac005",
